# Day 15 – Refactored Summarizer (Clean Code) ✨

## What it does
A fully refactored version of the Day 11 summarizer.
Reads a text file, generates an AI summary via Groq
(3 bullet points + main takeaway), and saves it.
Focus of this day was clean, professional code structure.

## Tech Stack
- Python 3
- groq
- python-dotenv

## Setup
pip install groq python-dotenv

# Create a .env file:
GROQ_API_KEY=your_key_here

## How to run
python refactored_scriptday11.py

# When prompted:
Enter the filename to summarise: notes.txt

## What I learned
- Module-level docstrings for professional documentation
- Function docstrings explaining purpose clearly
- Separating try/except blocks by responsibility
- Clean code principles: readable, documented, maintainable

## Output
Saves AI-generated summary to summary_[input_filename]
